    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1890-08-11T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1890-08-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="61"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d61">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Wharton</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Mizner</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1890-08-11">
                            <hi rend="italic">August</hi> 11, 1890</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 150.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I inclose for your information a copy of Mr.
                    Ryan’s No. 350, of the 24th ultimo, reporting that he had forwarded to you
                    Department’s cablegram of the 19th of the same month and inclosing copies of
                    telegrams relating to the war in Central America.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">William F. Wharton</hi>,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
